TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ahn, Dong-Hyun
AU  - Gao, Bin
T1  - A Parametric Nonlinear Model of Term Structure Dynamics
PY  - 1999
Y1  - 1999/07/02
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/12.4.721
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 12
IS  - 4
SP  - 721
EP  - 762
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Recent nonparametric estimation studies pioneered by Aït-Sahalia document that the diffusion of the short rate is similar to the parametric function, $r^{1.5},$ estimated by Chan et al., whereas the drift is substantially nonlinear in the short rate. These empirical properties call into question the efficacy of the existing affine term structure models and beg for alternative models which admit the observed behavior. This article presents such a model. Our model delivers closed-form solutions for bond prices and a concave relationship between the interest rate and the yields. We show that in empirical analyses, our model outperforms the one-factor affine models in both time-series as well as cross-sectional tests.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/12.4.721
ER  - 



